description:
src/server.rs lines 937-945 (index fn) and lines 1025-1048, 1052-1065 (serve_profile_html fn) use push-loops to build HTML strings:

    let mut personas_html = String::new();
    for (username, display_name) in &rows {
        personas_html.push_str(&format!(...));
    }

Per Rust standards: '.map().filter().collect() over push-loops.'

These would be clearer as:

    let personas_html: String = rows.iter().map(|(u, d)| format!(...)).collect();

Impact: Readability/idiom. The push-loop pattern is fine functionally but is non-idiomatic Rust. The same pattern appears in 3 locations in server.rs.
